# Legal Pages Review

After you **modify or add** anything that affects how the site works, what it collects, or what users agree to, check whether `src/content/pages/privacy-policy.html` and/or `src/content/pages/terms-of-service.html` need updates.

## Review when the change involves

- Contact forms, new form fields, or form providers (e.g. Netlify, reCAPTCHA)
- Analytics, tracking scripts, cookies, or local storage (beyond theme preference)
- Third-party embeds (maps, widgets, chat, reviews, payment links)
- New pages or features that collect personal or business information
- Pricing, subscriptions, contracts, refunds, or service terms
- Hosting, email, or data-sharing vendors
- Service area, business name, contact info, or licensing claims in `client.js`

## What to do

1. Read the current Privacy Policy and Terms of Service.
2. Update copy if the change creates a new collection, use, sharing, or obligation not already covered.
3. If no update is needed, say so briefly when finishing the task (e.g. "Legal pages: no change needed — copy-only edit").
4. Do not leave placeholder "template" language in client-facing legal pages.

## Legal page paths

- `src/content/pages/privacy-policy.html`
- `src/content/pages/terms-of-service.html`
